{"TopicId":154108,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Mk 3 Science lab","CreatedByName":"Thor Wotansen","CreatedById":157596,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-28T04:02:55Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Thor Wotansen","CreatedById":157596,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-28T04:02:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m a huge fan of spaceplanes and SSTOs, and I play KSP stock, parts wise.\u00A0 One thing I find lacking in the current stock parts list is a science lab that fits a spaceplane form factor.\u00A0 Sure, you can stuff a science lab inside a Mk 3 cargo bay, but that just adds to part count and complexity and also wastes a bunch of space.\u00A0 The Mk 3 passenger tank holds 16 kerbals, I don\u0027t think it would be too big a stretch to have a science lab version of it.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MinimalMinmus","CreatedById":172387,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-28T09:10:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore generally, IMHO there should be a science lab for 3.75m as well. Oh, and as we\u0027re talking \u0022bigger parts\u0022... 3.75m hitchhiker, anyone?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mystik","CreatedById":172088,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-28T09:52:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, would like to have a science lab on a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E, but could we make it shorter to fit one kerbal and stuff?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-12-28T09:52:33Z\u0022 title=\u002212/28/2016 09:52  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by mystik\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-28T11:36:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA tweakable for this\u00A0would be nice to have. You would simply right-click on the MK3 passanger module and switch its role to the lab.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Adelaar","CreatedById":150794,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-28T11:47:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222903057\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482924979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002239636\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Veeltch\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, Veeltch said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA tweakable for this\u00A0would be nice to have. You would simply right-click on the MK3 passanger module and switch its role to the lab.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Darnok","CreatedById":85708,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-28T12:05:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222902966\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022154108\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221482916215\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022172387\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MinimalMinmus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, MinimalMinmus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMore generally, IMHO there should be a science lab for 3.75m as well. Oh, and as we\u0027re talking \u0022bigger parts\u0022... 3.75m hitchhiker, anyone?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022331D24EF00000578-3535003-image-a-50_1460\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.dailymail.co.uk/i/pix/2016/04/12/22/331D24EF00000578-3535003-image-a-50_1460496929375.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}